    48	<!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->
    49	## What Was Built
    50	
    51	SKILL.md now presents the two use cases as co-equal lanes instead of an agent-improvement skill with a trailing model-benchmark mode. The "Mode 4: Model-Benchmark" subsection became a top-level Lane B section parallel to the Lane A agent-improvement section, and the smart-router learned to route benchmark phrasing.
    52	
    53	### Changes
    54	
    55	- §1 WHEN TO USE gained a "Two Co-Equal Lanes" table (Lane A improves an agent file via `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`, Lane B benchmarks a model or prompt framework via `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`) plus expanded activation triggers.
    56	- §2 SMART ROUTING gained a `MODEL_BENCHMARK` intent at weight 5 and a matching RESOURCE_MAP entry pointing at `references/workflow/benchmark_operator_guide.md` and `references/scoring/evaluator_contract.md` (both confirmed present).
    57	- §3 became `LANE A: AGENT-IMPROVEMENT` (modes 1, 2, 2A, 3 and the 5-dimension framework retained verbatim).
    58	- §4 became a co-equal `LANE B: MODEL-BENCHMARK` section carrying every prior detail: loop-host `--mode=model-benchmark`, the dispatch-model executor map, `--scorer pattern|5dim`, `--grader noop|mock|llm`, mode-aware records and promotion, and the `DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC` and `DEEP_AGENT_GRADER_CACHE_RAW` hardening gates.
    59	- §5 through §11 renumbered, §10 INTEGRATION POINTS labeled both lane entry points.
    60	
    61	### Files Changed
    62	
    63	| File | Action | Purpose |
    64	|------|--------|---------|
    65	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` | Modified | Two co-equal lanes + MODEL_BENCHMARK router intent + RESOURCE_MAP entry |
    66	<!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->
    67	
    68	---
    69	
    70	<!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->
    71	## How It Was Delivered
    72	
    73	A restructure agent reframed the headings and added the router intent while preserving all factual content (the diff was 33 insertions, 14 deletions, every deletion a renumber or relabel). An independent verifier confirmed DQI, no-ToC, the two-lane structure, the router intent, and information preservation. The 009 phase docs were scaffolded in parallel.
    74	<!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->
    75	
    76	---
    77	
    78	<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->
    79	## Key Decisions
    80	
    81	| Decision | Why |
    82	|----------|-----|
    83	| Treat model-benchmark as a co-equal lane, not a mode | The command layer already ships two co-equal entry points, so the doc should match that reality |
    84	| MODEL_BENCHMARK router weight 5 | One above the existing weight-4 intents, so explicit benchmark phrasing wins ambiguity ties |
    85	| Reframe, do not rewrite | Preserve every shipped runtime detail, change only structure and headings |
    86	<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->
