.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.7.0.0.md:1:This release is a documentation release-cleanup pass that brings the deep-agent-improvement skill to current sk-doc template and HVR standards before the broader 131 evolution arc consumes it. The README is rewritten to a marketing-leaning voice anchored at roughly 70% of the root README intensity, with the structure section regenerated to list all 15 references and all 14 scripts. Surgical alignment fixes landed across SKILL.md and two reference files, the Smart Router section was left untouched, and a set of lower-priority deviations were logged and deferred with rationale. The work ran as a five-phase release-cleanup packet with a blocking human-approval gate before any deep-research pass.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.7.0.0.md:3:> Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/116-deep-skill-evolution/000-release-cleanup/005-deep-agent-improvement` (Level 3)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.7.0.0.md:53:The full audit ledger lives at `005-deep-agent-improvement/audit-findings.jsonl`, schema-validated against its `schemas/audit-finding.schema.json`. Of nine findings, six resolved and three deferred with rationale, with zero P0 or P1 findings left open.
