.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:1:This release lands the deep-agent-improvement portion of the packets 108 plus 110 auto-review uplift program. One reusable teaching from the upstream `dzianisv/opencode-plugins` auto-review package now applies to the mutation-coverage pipeline: a signature-based dedup that prevents the same mutation from being proposed twice across iterations of the same improvement arc. The signature is stored alongside each mutation in `mutation-coverage.json`. The council was explicit in section 10.6 that the authoritative storage IS `mutation-coverage.json`, NOT `agent-improvement-state.jsonl`, so the replay consumer and the coverage reducer share one source of truth. Every mechanism cleared a 5-of-5 unanimous deep-ai-council review by `cli-codex gpt-5.5 xhigh fast` before any code shipped.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:63:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/mutation-coverage.cjs` | New `computeMutationSignature(mutation)` function returning `sha256(dimension + ":" + mutationType + ":" + targetSection + ":" + normalized_body.slice(0,64))`. Pre-propose check against existing `mutations[]` signatures. Skipped proposals record `EXHAUSTED-FROM: iter-NNN`. Signatures stored on each entry in `mutation-coverage.json` (council section 10.6: authoritative storage is `mutation-coverage.json`, NOT `agent-improvement-state.jsonl`). Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:64:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Reducer updated to recognize the new `signature` field. Backward-compatible fallthrough when the field is absent. Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:70:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` | Documents the signature scheme, the `DEEP_AGENT_IMPROVEMENT_SKIP_DEDUP=1` env-var bypass, and the `EXHAUSTED-FROM:` skip-reason format. Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:71:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/07--runtime-truth/034-replay-consumer.md` | New manual playbook scenario verifying that the replay consumer respects signature dedup. Touched in b29640496. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/manual_testing_playbook/09--model-benchmark-mode/037-optin-5dim-scorer.md:45:| MB-037 | Opt-In 5-Dimension Scorer | Validate Opt-In 5-Dimension Scorer | `Validate that the opt-in 5dim scorer stamps scoringMethod: 5dim and emits D1-D5 dimension scores per fixture.` | rm -rf /tmp/mb-037 &amp;&amp; mkdir -p /tmp/mb-037 &amp;&amp; \<br>node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs \<br>  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \<br>  --outputs-dir /tmp/mb-037 ; \<br>node .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs \<br>  --profile .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-profiles/default.json \<br>  --outputs-dir /tmp/mb-037 \<br>  --output /tmp/mb-037/report.json \<br>  --scorer 5dim \<br>  --grader noop | Benchmark completes with exit code 0; `report.json` has `status: "benchmark-complete"`; `report.json` has `scoringMethod: "5dim"`; each `fixtures[]` entry has `scoringMethod: "5dim"` and a `dimensions` object with keys `D1`-`D5`; each dimension value is numeric in `0.0`-`1.0`; `D4` equals `1.0` under noop; appended `benchmark_run` row carries `scoringMethod: "5dim"` and `mode: "model-benchmark"` | `terminal transcript, command output, generated files, and PASS/FAIL verdict` | Output has `scoringMethod: "5dim"` with a per-fixture `dimensions` object containing D1-D5 numeric scores and `D4: 1.0` under noop -- confirming the opt-in 5-dim scorer routes through the ported scorer and stays deterministic. | If `scoringMethod` is `pattern`: confirm `--scorer 5dim` was passed and check the scorer selection in `run-benchmark.cjs`<br>If `dimensions` is missing or has fewer than 5 keys: inspect `scoreFixture5dim()` and the `dimensions` mapping in `score-model-variant.cjs`<br>If `D4` is not `1.0`: confirm `--grader noop` was used; `mock` and `llm` graders produce different D4 values<br>If a `require` error references the scorer tree: confirm `scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs` exists and resolves |
