.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/agent-improvement/score_dimensions.md:21:The 5-dimension scoring rubric is the core evaluation framework for deep-agent-improvement. It measures agent quality across five weighted dimensions: structural integrity, rule coherence, integration consistency, output quality, and system fitness. Each dimension is scored 0-100, then combined using dimension weights to produce a final weighted score.
