.opencode/skills/deep-ai-council/changelog/v1.3.0.0.md:14:The council skill is rejoining the `deep-*` family alongside `deep-review`, `deep-research`, `deep-agent-improvement`, and `deep-loop-runtime`, following the 130 research verdict and user intent. This is a point-release in the v1.x single-round-council era because it renames the skill package without changing the runtime model. The runtime agent remains `ai-council` because agent identity is already decoupled from the skill folder slug.
.opencode/skills/deep-ai-council/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:69:`README.md` follows the HVR (Human-Visible Reference) shape used by `deep-research`, `deep-review`, and `deep-agent-improvement`: ten numbered sections from Overview through Related Documents, three concrete usage examples (top-level dispatch, `@orchestrate` at Depth 1, CLI-skill capture), the runtime parity table for all four mirrors, and a troubleshooting matrix.
