.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.0.0.md:160:**Concrete example.** The query `"5-dimension agent scoring"` used to misroute to `sk-prompt` at 0.77 confidence via a weak keyword hit on `scoring`. After the fix it routes to `sk-deep-agent-improvement` at 0.95.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.1.0.md:319:- `@improve-agent` → **`@deep-agent-improvement`**, completes the family alignment with the underlying `deep-agent-improvement` skill and the `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command. 8 file renames + 54 active references.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.1.0.md:477:- **`@improve-agent`** → **`@deep-agent-improvement`**. External callers must update.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:88:No systematic way to evaluate agent prompt files. Manual review was inconsistent and could not track improvement over time. Created `sk-deep-agent-improvement` with 8 scripts: `scan-integration.cjs` discovers all surfaces an agent touches (main, mirrors, commands, YAML, skills); `generate-profile.cjs` derives scoring from any agent's own rules; `score-candidate.cjs` scores across 5 weighted dimensions (structural 0.20, ruleCoherence 0.25, integration 0.25, outputQuality 0.15, systemFitness 0.15). All scoring is deterministic -- regex, string matching, file-existence checks -- no LLM-as-judge.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:93:Editing main agent files directly during evaluation is dangerous -- a bad change could break the agent. The `@agent-improver` subagent writes candidates to a packet-local runtime area, never touching main targets. The `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command orchestrates the full loop: scan, profile, candidate, score, benchmark, reduce, stop-check. Promotion requires passing all evidence gates plus explicit operator approval.
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:133:| `sk-deep-agent-improvement/scripts/score-candidate.cjs` | 5-dimension framework with `--dynamic` flag |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:134:| `sk-deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scan-integration.cjs` | Integration surface scanner |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:135:| `sk-deep-agent-improvement/scripts/generate-profile.cjs` | Dynamic profile generator |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:136:| `sk-deep-agent-improvement/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Dimensional tracking, configurable plateau, accepted counting fix |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:137:| `sk-deep-agent-improvement/scripts/run-benchmark.cjs` | Fixture benchmark with integration report |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:139:| `.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md` | Full command rewrite (430+ lines) |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md:149:No migration required. Both programs are additive. The code graph, hooks, and bootstrap surfaces are backward compatible. The `sk-deep-agent-improvement` skill is entirely new and does not affect existing workflows. The `plateauWindow` config field defaults to 3 (same as previous hardcoded value). If you had custom references to `sk-recursive-agent`, update them to `sk-deep-agent-improvement`.
